## Introduction
My individual data collection focused on understanding my personal eating and satiety patterns over time. I was interested in the fact that I often feel hungry shortly after eating, and I wanted to investigate what might be influencing this.

I included examining how different food types and portion sizes affected my fullness duration, and whether physical activity played a role in changing these patterns.

Across multiple days and meals, I recorded:

* the time I started feeling hungry
* the time of my previous meal
* the type of food I consumed
* portion size
* my self-reported fullness level after eating
* whether I engaged in any physical activity between meals (and if yes what type)

Over time, this created a data set that can be seen as a personal observation of my digestion and satiety response under different conditions.
