### What I tried but found did not work

**One issue I encountered was trying to calculate the time difference between 'time_when_hungry' and 'time_of_last_meal'. **<br>
At first, I tried using: 

`difftime(time_when_hungry, time_of_last_meal, units = "mins")`

directly, but it did not work because my variables only contained times (eg 10:00:00) and not full date-time values. Since `difftime()` requires complete date-time objects, I solved this by temporarily pasting a dummy date onto both time variables before calculating the difference.

**Another issue occurred in the portion_size_vs_fullness_duration_plot.** <br>
Initially, I tried using only the summarised exercise dataset for the entire graph, but later realised it only contained two rows and could not represent the full distribution of observations. I therefore used the raw dataset for the jittered points and only used the summarised data for the mean points.
