## Learning reflection

One important idea I learned from Module 4 was how much the choice and layering of visualisations can affect the way data is interpreted and communicated. I learned that different chart types are useful for showing different kinds of relationships, and that combining multiple geoms or variables within the same graph can make a visualisation much more informative and expressive.

For example, using colour intensity, jittered observations, and summary layers together allowed me to communicate several dimensions of information within a single graph rather than separating everything into multiple simpler charts. I started to understand that effective visualisations are not only about displaying data efficiently, but also about helping tell a clearer and more engaging story.

This project also made me more curious about exploring more advanced data visualisation techniques and data transformation methods in R.

